1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,600
Science has a clearer story about the worked examples effect than social media does.

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:12,000
The worked examples effect suggests people learn better from guided examples than from solving problems alone.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,200
It’s like having a map versus wandering aimlessly.

4
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,800
Which would you choose?

5
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:22,800
Studies show worked examples not only save time but reduce cognitive load, making learning easier.

6
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:26,800
So, if you want to learn effectively, start with examples.

7
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:27,600
It’s science!

